The unusual, fragmented nature of the re­ ported T . rex sequence does not make it ame­ nable to standard, model-based phylogenetic analysis. Instead, we examined the phylogenetic signal of the a1(I) frag­ ments of mastodon and T . rex using Neighbor- Net analysis and uncor­ rected genetic distances. Using the sequences reported in ( 13 ), both the T . rex and masto­ don signal display an affinity with amphibians (
). Our reinter­ pretation of the spectra (12) changes the affinity of mastodon but not of T . rex (
). In addition to the a1(I) peptides used in the Neighbor-Net analysis, Asara et al . reported two other peptides from T . rex ( 13 ); we question the interpretation of the a1( II ) spectra (identical to frog) but not the a2(I) spectra (identical to chicken).

